<div class="home-about">
  <p>
    Hi, I'm Michael. I'm a Senior AI Research Engineer at
    <a href="https://www.mitre.org">The MITRE Corporation</a> in San Diego,
    where I work on natural language processing, large language models, computer
    vision, and reinforcement learning. I've published research at NAACL, NeurIPS,
    AMTA, and SPIE, and I build open-source tools like
    <a href="https://github.com/mitrefireline/simfire">SimFire</a> (a wildfire
    simulator for RL research) and
    <a href="https://github.com/janus-llm">Janus</a> (an LLM code understanding
    library).
  </p>
  <p>
    I studied electrical engineering at the University of San Diego, picked up
    minors in math and physics along the way, and have been building ML systems
    for government and research applications since 2018.
  </p>
